rough some unrelated path. Hmm, that could be fine, but I need to be careful about unintended captures! It's definitely something to keep in mind moving forward.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Updated the active-class test to explicitly reach the remaining synthetic dynamic-access call site.\n\nChanged:\n\n- `tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/src/test/java/io_rest_assured/rest_assured/ResponseSpecificationImplInnerHamcrestAssertionClosure_validateHeadersAndCookies_closure6Test.java`\n\nWhat changed:\n\n- Keeps the public Rest Assured cookie-validation path using a local `HttpServer`.\n- Captures the generated Groovy cookie validation closure for:\n  - `io.restassured.internal.ResponseSpecificationImpl$_HamcrestAssertionClosure_validateHeadersAndCookies_closure6`\n- Invokes its generated static `class$` method through Groovy’s `MetaClass`, matching the existing pattern used by nearby generated closure tests.\n- This should exercise:\n  - `java.lang.Class#forName(java.lang.String)`\n  - from `ResponseSpecificationImpl$_HamcrestAssertionClosure_validateHeadersAndCookies_closure6.class$`\n\nI did not run compilation or tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0100aefe31cace74016a27a9ffe324819092fa252ba76252db\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1630, "output": 958, "cacheRead": 53760, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 56348, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1780984299367, "responseId": "resp_0100aefe31cace74016a27a9ebfe8c819094cdc2a8176792e1"}}
